theorem Topology.closure_union_closure_eq_closure_union {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (closure A ∪ closure B) = closure (A ∪ B) := by
  -- We prove the equality by showing mutual inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- First, show `closure (closure A ∪ closure B) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`.
    -- Since `closure A ∪ closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`, taking closures preserves the inclusion.
    have h_sub : closure A ∪ closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hxA =>
          -- `closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`
          exact
            (closure_mono (Set.subset_union_left : A ⊆ A ∪ B)) hxA
      | inr hxB =>
          -- `closure B ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`
          exact
            (closure_mono (Set.subset_union_right : B ⊆ A ∪ B)) hxB
    exact closure_mono h_sub
  · -- Conversely, show `closure (A ∪ B) ⊆ closure (closure A ∪ closure B)`.
    -- Start with the known identity `closure (A ∪ B) = closure A ∪ closure B`.
    have h_eq : closure (A ∪ B) = closure A ∪ closure B := by
      simpa using closure_union A B
    -- The set `closure A ∪ closure B` is contained in its own closure.
    have h_sub : closure A ∪ closure B ⊆ closure (closure A ∪ closure B) := by
      intro x hx
      exact subset_closure hx
    -- Rewrite using `h_eq` and conclude.
    simpa [h_eq] using h_sub

theorem Topology.closure_diff_subset_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A \ B) ⊆ closure A := by
  exact closure_mono (Set.diff_subset : A \ B ⊆ A)
